Subject: Re: [T2] 77 Westy exhaust and fan housing attachment

On 6/5/06 1:51 PM, "courtney hook" <courtneyhook(-at-)shaw.ca> wrote:

> My muffler on my 77 westy just broke right off at the heaterbox triangle,
> leaving it's triangle piece still attached to the heater box. The strap that
> goes up to the alum. fan  housing assembly is what is leaving it from dropping
> down. I went to remove the bolt on the fan housing to remove the strap but it
> is just turning around and around.
> What I need to know is whether that is a tapped hole in the housing (that is
> prob stripped now), or is it a nut and bolt that goes right through? Surely it
> is a threaded hole in the housing?? The reason the muffler prob broke there is
> the strap was loose from the P.O. and when I started to investigate found it
> couldn't be tightened, just spins.
> Thanks, 
> Courtney

It is a threaded hole. With the eliminator muffler the hole is always
stripped, the magnesium can't take the weight. When I do those eliminator
mufflers, I re-tap the hole and put a stud in there, then a nut. The stud
makes the connection much stronger.


